Text.string: Blood feud! Hrgh, hrgh. Just practicing.
Thank you for saving me. Y'know, if you hadn't come along, I might be dead, which is not my preferred state of existence, thank you.
Pssht. I'd be a way better bandit god. Just saying.
Man, I never thought I'd be runnin' and gunnin' with Lilith again. Firehawk best hawk!
Hiya, friend. Can I interest you in a partially-used bloody skull?
Go Sun Smashers! Sorry, force of habit, my bad. Crying now.
That's one hell of a ship you guys got there! You know, I'd ask to come on board and fly around space with ya, but um... I'm not gonna.

You're going to Promethea? I heard through the ear-vine that my old friend Rhys has been doing great work bringing Atlas back from the brink of total ruin. If you see him, tell him Vaughn said, “What up, bro?”
Man... if Tyreen could do that to the FIREHAWK, what would her powers do to ME? I mean, what's a guy supposed to do against power like that?

I mean, I'm not saying I'm into this whole “Tyreen is actually a god” thing, but... I can kinda see how she tricked some of the, uh, simpler, for lack of a kinder word, bandit folks into thinking that.
You go out there and take the fight to the Calypsos wherever they go. I will stay here and keep working on bringing back the Pandora that I know and love.
Wait-wait-wait-wait-wait... Typhon? Typhon DeLeon? He's alive?! Damn! That guy's even cooler than I thought!
Oh sure, just off to the fabled lost Eridian planet of Nekrotafeyo, huh? Just another day in the exciting life of a Vault Hunter, I guess.
Bring me back something nice from Nekrotafeyo, okay? Like a big old hunk of weird alien meat or a mug with my name on it, I don't know, just... something.
New Sirens poppin' up all over the place lately, huh? Ava seems like good people, though. Couldn't have happened to a nicer kid.
So Tyreen thinks she's already won, huh? Well, well, well, isn't she in for a rude awakening when you show up to poop on her parade! Literally!
If I had my druthers, it woulda been Tyreen who got dead, but taking out Troy is a good start.
So, the entire planet is doomed, yeah? Man, I really shoulda seen that comin'. Why does every good thing have to come to an end? Oh, life.
Yeesh, Typhon's their father? I guess sometimes the apple falls very, very far from the tree.

Some big Eridian machine is supposed to save us all? I mean, I don't know... Didn't the Eridians kinda get us into this whole mess in the first place? Stupid aliens messing up my planet from behind their civilization-sized grave! Gah!

I should probably be scared for my life down here, uh, what with an entire planet breaking open like a monster egg and all, but—I don't know. I mean, I got a good feeling about you. You know what? I'm pretty sure you'll figure it out.
What a shock, by the way, that the Great Vault didn't turn out to be the perfect bandit heaven the Calypsos were peddling.
These quakes are really starting to get annoying. I even spilled my tea earlier.
This is it! Okay, now I know I said that it was “it” before, but uh, now it's really it. No, this is ”it” it. Let's not mince its.

Tyreen has gone too far! Trying to wreck my favorite planet, all so she can leech some horrible monster from beyond the stars or whatever. Well, it's not gonna happen! I'm assuming! Because you will take care of it!
Man... Tyreen killed her own father? Ah, that is beyond cold. I mean, I guess we know who the REAL Vault Monster is.
I thought Tyreen was crazy before, but now she has gone full cookoo bird whackjob. But not the fun kind. The scary kind!

So, what do you think? What do you think's gonna happen if Tyreen, y'know... wins? Not that I think she will, of course, I have full confidence in you. Just... if she did happen to, do you think I should get off the planet? Or...
Wow. That was heroic as hell! You guys really came through for me! I mean, y'know, for the universe and stuff too, but me specifically. Good work, bro!
We always knew Tyreen was a monster, but sheesh did she take it to a whole other level!
You know, I smell an opportunity here. Hear me out. The COV in disarray, a new Pandora on the horizon... hmm... Time to reclaim the mantle of Bandit King Vaughn! In theatres this fall.
It's beautiful, isn't it? That... thing Lilith left in the sky. Whatever that is. [sigh] I sure hope she's out there somewhere.
So, what now? What, do you, like, ride off into the sunset or...?
Bro! It's been an indeterminate amount of time! So... how dem Raiders?
Why are you checking in with me? Don't you have, like, big important business to attend to? Like, elsewhere?
So, what do you think of my outfit? Be honest. It's pretty great, right?
I miss having a clan, y'know? Just being out here on my own, it just doesn't feel right. I need a community to order around.
Hypothetical. If you came across a severed hand holding a flower... what would you do? Asking for a friend.
What? It's not like I've never gathered a new clan before. Losing your whole clan to some horrible tragedy and starting all over again is just what we call the Pandoran Shuffle.
Hey, does this cape make my butt look big? I mean, I think it does, but like in a good way. You know? Like, bam! Glutes!
Y'know, I wish I had a cool nickname like “Firehawk”. Wonder what mine would be... like Stonewolf, or... Underwear Chief.
I hate the Calypsos! Y'know, I didn't become a bandit to be told what to do or who to kill, ya know?
Blood feuuuuuuuud! Sorry, I just have to shout that every once in a while. It's good for the bandit soul.
If I'm being ENTIRELY honest, Tyreen Calypso scares the bejeebus outta me. But I'm sure you won't let that stop you! Right? 'Cause you're like... a big hero or something... right?
Bandit life was a lot more fun before the Children of the Vault came along and ruined everything with their stupid cult.
The Calypsos turned a beautiful chaos of bandit freedom into a terrible chaos of bandit servitude! It is not right, I tells ya!
Hey, Vault Hunter! Did you meet my buddy Rhys? What's his address? I've got a bloody skull with his name on it.

You're back! Oh man, I have been so lonely! Like crying myself to sleep against my old rock pillow lonely! I mean, a man can only talk to his pecs for so long. You know, the other night I cried so much that I wore the rock down to sand. Sand! So... that's my whole thing.
You're alive! Squee! Bandit lyyyyyyfe!
You look sad. I can smell it. No, no-no-no, don't wash it off. Learn from it. Bandit wisdom.
How's it going? You didn't forget about me, did ya? 'Cause I won't let ya! Hahahaha... I'm kidding but I am following you.
You smell like swamp and lizards! Pretty hot.
You know, if there's one thing I can say about Carnivora, it's this: those dudes are not messing around. That is one big bad bandit death party on wheels, brother. You better watch your glutes.
Welcome back! Pandora missed you. Or maybe that was just me. I don't know, who can keep track anymore out here, but it feels like Pandora missed you, too, I don't—where are you going?
So, how's the ship? Couldn't help but notice I wasn't uh, you know, ever invited.
So anyway, how was your trip? Promethea and Eden-6, right? How were they, nice? Full of bad guys to shoot? Awesome. Well, thanks for not inviting me. Dick.
I heard they have dinosaurs on Eden-6, is that true? Man, that's rad! Did you eat any of 'em? I bet they're just like, big, rubbery murder chickens.

Wait, Tannis is a Siren? Wait. Wait-wait-wait-wait. Wasn't she already, like, a super-genius? Why does she get both of those things? That is no fair! I don't even have one thing except for my excuisitely-sculpted body and aptitude for numbers!

Look, y'know, if I'm being honest, I—yes, I was a little sad to see Carnivora taken out like that. I mean, sure, it's a giant COV monstrosity full of braindead cultist weirdos, but... it was pretty great, too.
So, bro, you ready for the big showdown? Because it sure seems like it's time to kill those Calypsos and put a stop to all this.

Oh, by the way, how's my old buddy Rhys doing? Y'know, we haven't really talked much since we took out the Traveler and opened up a Vault together. We just kinda grew apart, y'know, and that happens sometimes when you're adulting and you go one direction and then things get in the way, you have a schedule, you have a family of rocks... Uh, he went full-corporate, I guess, and I, um... I'm just real.

Okay, can I, um... Can I get real with you for a second? Look, I don't wanna make this weird, but... I believe in you, Vault Hunter. I know you can—no, look at me! I know you can beat the living snot out of those damn Calypsos and get this place back on the right wrong track! Okay, I believe in you!||—Stop looking at me.
Way to take out that Shiv jerk! Thought he was cool just because he had a big knife... sword... thing.
Oof. Good luck getting that map back. I don't go anywhere near that Holy Broadcasting Center if I can help it. That's crazy-cult central right there.
So, how's Nekrotafeyo? Pretty weird, I bet. Right?
Hey, got your hands on another Vault Key, huh? Pretty cool. Hope it works!
Tyreen has no idea what's coming her way. You are a force of nature, bro!
Hard to believe it's really over. But you did it. You really freakin' did it!
It's hot! Does anyone else think it's really hot today? Oh, it's hot. I'm just sweating in the weirdest places.
It's the Vault Hunterrr... Hunty-huntery-hunter, yeaaaaah.
So, you're out there saving the universe and stuff, huh? Yeah, that's pretty cool, I guess. I'm good though, just—y'know, chillin'.
Don't you worry about me. I got a belly full of skag meat and a warm place to sleep. What more does a guy need?
Hmm... How long's it been since I had this cape washed?
Whoa, you took out Mouthpiece?! That is a serious piece of freaking business right there! Good on ya, Vault Hunter!
Lilith? Oh yeah, Lilith and me go way back, and, uh... well, I hope she's okay. No, you know what? I KNOW she'll be okay! Powers or not, she's still the freakin' Firehawk!
Ah, got your ship all fixed up, did ya? Very cool, bro. Very cool. Time for you to soar, and me to keep my feet right here in the Pandoran dirt.

Did you see Rhys?! How's he lookin'? Does he look well? Like is he eating enough? Oh my god, he's a grown man, I'm sure he's okay. Oh, he's so grown up! Is he okay? Tell me he's okay. Did he ask about me?
Hey, you're back! And you smell like swamp ass! That's a compliment.
That was the coolest nightmare on wheels I've ever seen! Oh, but, uh, you know, good job taking it down, too.
Woohoo! That is the stuff legends are made of! Holy crap-sauce, that was one hell of a ride!
See ya never, Troy! Boom! One Calypso down, one to giggity-go!
Got a gig for you, Vault Hunter.
Need some work? I've got something.
Got something here that needs doing here, Vault Hunter.
Hey, hey!
Hey bro.
S'up, Vault Hunter?
Why, hello Vault Hunter! And how are you today?
Yo, bro.
Duuuude.
Ah, sunlight. The great equalizer.
I feel like I should be sleeping. Do I do that?
Moon party anyone?
Got a job for you.
Got a thing that needs doin'. You in?
Yo, bro, I have a mission of the utmost consequence!
Gig for you, if you've got the time.
Need some extra cash? 'Cause I've got a job with your name on it.
How's that thing going?
You doing that thing I asked you to do?
How goes the mission?
Hope that job's going well.
You almost done with that job?
Yeah, later.
All right, catch you later, bro.
Bro, you heading out, bro?
Kay. See ya.
Yep, adi-bros.
Catch you on the flip, bro!
Peace, amig-bro!
It's been real!
Good talk.
I enjoy our little chats.
